Class JobDescriptor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.fermitech.jocasta.core.JobDescriptor

  • public class JobDescriptor
extends java.lang.Object
    This is the JobDescriptor class, the class that contains the queue of jobs to perform on a particular file.

    • Constructor Detail

      • JobDescriptor

        public JobDescriptor(FileInputOptions options,
                     java.lang.String src_path,
                     java.lang.String dst_path,
                     int id)
        This is one of the two constructor of the JobDescriptor class. This one is intended to work as the constructor of a JobDescriptor whose file needs to be archived. If something is wrong, the JobDescriptor is marked as faulty.
        Parameters:
        options - the JPanel element in which the user defines the nature of the jobs.
        src_path - the string containing the path of the file.
        dst_path - the string containing the destination of the file.
        id - the identification number of the JobDescriptor.

      • JobDescriptor

        public JobDescriptor(java.lang.String src_path,
                     java.lang.String dst_path,
                     java.lang.String password,
                     int id)
        This is one of the two constructor of the JobDescriptor class. This one is intended to work as the constructor of a JobDescriptor whose file needs to be unarchived. Based on the extension, it enables the different jobs.
        Parameters:
        src_path - the string containing the path of the file.
        dst_path - the string containing the destination of the file.
        password - the password.
        id - the identification number of the JobDescriptor.
